ed into three core business segments general insurance global life and farmers zurich employs around  people serving customers in more than  countries and territories around the globe the company is listed on the six swiss exchange as of  it had shareholders equity of  billion contents  history  core business segments  general insurance  global life  farmers  corporate social responsibility  financial performanceinformation  criticism  references  external links historyedit the company was founded in  as a marine reinsurance under the name versicherungsverein insurance association a subsidiary of the schweiz marine company in  after a number of acquisitions it was unified to form one holding company – zurich financial services in april  zurich financial services ltd changed its name to zurich insurance group ltd in a statement the group explained the rationale behind the name change in recognition of this strategic focus the reference to financial services in the company name has been replaced by indicating the insurance activity of the group instead and to specify the purpose accordingly in december  the groups ceo martin senn who committed suicide on may   announced his resignation despite years of highly profitable business operations the focus was put on recent events which forced mr senn to step down adinterim chairman tom de swaan took over as acting ceo on  january  it was announced that zurich had poached mario greco ceo of generali as its next chief executive and that he would start on  may core business segmentsedit general insuranceedit zurichs general insurance business serves individuals small and mediumsized businesses and major multinational corporations with motor home and commercial products and services global lifeedit zurichs global life business offers life insurance savings investment and pension products in the united states life insurance is issued by zurich american life insurance company with offices in schaumburg illinois and new york city farmersedit zurichs farmers segment includes farmers management services which provides nonclaims related management services to the farmers exchanges not owned by zurich as well as the farmers re business which includes reinsurance assumed from the farmers exchange by the group zurich’s farmers insurance group is the third largest insurance group in the united states corporate social responsibilityedit in  zurich was awarded charity times best insurance services and was shortlisted again in  in  the zurich community trust uk won the cross sector partnership of the year award for its partnership with the treatment charity addaction according to its website zurich community trust has donated over £ million since  with the goal of addressing key social issues it has supported over  charities a year making a measurable impact on the lives of over  people zurich was one of the first recipients of the community mark from business in the community which it has successfully retained for three years at a group level the z zurich foundations mission is to help individuals and communities understand and manage risk leveraging zurichs core strengths as an insurer zurich is achieving this aim by working with longterm partnership with select nonprofit organizations such as practical action the rainforest alliance and the international federation of red cross and red crescent societies in march  zurich reinforced its commitment to the z zurich foundation by making a substantial investment of  million in  zurich launched a free online resource – my community starter – designed to make getting involved in community activities more simple on  october  zurich north america hosted a ceremony at the  tribute center honoring the winners of its  kamp awards a program created as a living legacy to the four employees killed on  john keohane peggy alario kathy moran and ludwig picarro in march  zurich announced its global flood resilience program which aims to enhance community flood resilience by finding innovative ways to increase the impact of disaster risk reduction efforts at community national and global levels the first country program is taking place in mexico and indonesia to maximize the community impact of the program zurich has formed a strategic alliance with the international federation of red cross and red crescent societies ifrc financial performanceinformationedit zurich offices in madrid spain zurich insurance group ltd zurich is listed on the six swiss exchange under the ticker zurn as of  december  there were  fully paid registered shares and  shareholders  of the holding of the registered shares were private individuals  of all outstanding shares  were foundations and pension funds  of all outstanding shares and  were other legal entities  of all outstanding shares in its full year results for  zurich reported a net income after tax attributable to shareholders of  billion an increase of  on the previous year and a business operating profit of  billion a full year dividend of chf  per share was approved at the annual general meeting the company has a solvency  ratio of  as of  december  and a swiss solvency test ratio of  as of  july  far above the minimum capital requirements the strength of zurich’s balance sheet is reflected in the reports of the ratings agencies as of  december  zurich was rated as ‘aastable’ by standard  poors ‘aastable’ by moodys and astable’ by am best all figures below are for the year ended  december and are in usd millions unless stated otherwise year ended  december revenue m business operating profit bop m income attributable to shareholders m basic earnings per share chf           criticismedit in  zurich financial services settled a  million case relating to bid rigging and price fixing in the united states businesses shopping for commercial insurance were deceived into believing they were getting the best deals available said abbott the whole anticompetitive scheme was an intentional smoke screen by